  "answer": "## Answer\n\n**Agentic RAG** is a retrieval-augmented generation pattern where an LLM acts more like an autonomous agent: it can **plan**, **decide when and what to retrieve**, **rewrite queries**, **use tools**, and **iterate over multiple retrieval/reasoning steps** before answering. In contrast, **standard RAG** is usually a mostly fixed pipeline: **retrieve relevant context once, append it to the prompt, then generate the answer**. ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/concepts/retrieval-augmented-generation?utm_source=openai))\n\nPractically, agentic RAG is useful for **complex, multi-hop, or ambiguous questions** because the system can refine its search as it learns more. The tradeoff is **more latency, higher cost, and more orchestration complexity**, plus more opportunities for compounding mistakes across steps. Standard RAG is simpler, cheaper, and easier to control, but it can struggle when one retrieval pass is not enough. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/abs/2501.09136?utm_source=openai))\n\n## Sources\n\n- Microsoft Learn — *Retrieval augmented generation (RAG) and indexes in Microsoft Foundry*: standard RAG as search + grounding context + generation. ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/concepts/retrieval-augmented-generation?view=foundry-classic&utm_source=openai))\n- Microsoft Learn — *What is agentic RAG?*: basic vs agentic RAG overview. ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/shows/ai-agents-for-beginners/what-is-agentic-rag?utm_source=openai))\n- arXiv survey — *Agentic Retrieval-Augmented Generation: A Survey on Agentic RAG*: agentic RAG uses planning, reflection, tool use, and multi-agent collaboration. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/abs/2501.09136?utm_source=openai))\n- arXiv — *A-RAG: Scaling Agentic Retrieval-Augmented Generation via Hierarchical Retrieval Interfaces*: agentic RAG exposes retrieval tools and lets the model participate in retrieval decisions. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.03442?utm_source=openai))\n\n## Limitations\n\n- This is a high-level summary, not a full taxonomy of agentic RAG variants.\n- “Agentic RAG” is not a single standardized architecture; different papers use the term differently. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/abs/2501.09136?utm_source=openai))",
